## 📋 Step-by-Step Execution Guide

### STEP 1: Setup (First time only - 5 minutes)

```r
# Install required packages
install.packages(c(
  "tidyverse",   # Data manipulation & ggplot2
  "car",         # VIF analysis
  "multcomp",    # Tukey HSD
  "pROC",        # ROC curves
  "caret",       # Confusion matrix
  "boot",        # Bootstrap
  "corrplot",    # Correlation plots
  "GGally",      # Scatterplot matrix
  "gridExtra",   # Multi-panel plots
  "broom"        # Tidy model outputs
))
```

### STEP 2: Generate Data (5 seconds)

```r
# Creates jm1.csv and kc1.csv in data/raw/
source("GENERATE_NASA_DATA.R")

# Verify files created:
file.exists("data/raw/jm1.csv")  # Should be TRUE
file.exists("data/raw/kc1.csv")  # Should be TRUE
```

### STEP 3: Run Analyses (Run in order!)

```r
# Script 1: Data Prep (~30 seconds)
source("01_data_preparation.R")
# ✓ Creates defect_data_clean.rds in data/processed/
# ✓ Prints requirement compliance check

# Script 2: EDA (~1 minute)
source("02_exploratory_analysis.R")
# ✓ Creates Figures 1-6
# ✓ Creates descriptive statistics tables

# Script 3: Multiple Regression (~30 seconds)
source("03_multiple_regression.R")
# ✓ Prints R², Adj R², coefficients, VIF
# ✓ Creates Figure 7 (diagnostics)
# ✓ **COPY VALUES FROM CONSOLE FOR REPORT**

# Script 4: ANOVA (~30 seconds)
source("04_anova.R")
# ✓ Prints F-statistic, p-value, η²
# ✓ Creates Figure 8 (violin plot)
# ✓ **COPY VALUES FROM CONSOLE FOR REPORT**

# Script 5: Logistic Regression (~30 seconds)
source("05_logistic_regression.R")
# ✓ Prints Odds Ratios, AUC, Accuracy, Sensitivity, Specificity
# ✓ Creates Figure 9 (ROC curve)
# ✓ **COPY VALUES FROM CONSOLE FOR REPORT**

# Script 6: Bootstrap & Permutation (~5-10 minutes - SLOWEST!)
source("06_bootstrap_permutation.R")
# ✓ Prints bootstrap CIs, permutation p-value
# ✓ Creates Figures 10-11
# ✓ **COPY VALUES FROM CONSOLE FOR REPORT**
```

**TOTAL TIME: ~15 minutes**

